By {{yearlink|1479}}, Gaskur had served Marlin Stormserpent for six or seven seasons.{{cite book/Elminster Must Die/MMP|187|18}}

Gaskur accompanied Marlin Stormserpent in his foray to [[Dragonskull Chamber]] of [[Castle Obarskyr]], where he stayed out the door while Marlin experimented with the control of [[Blueflame ghost]]s using the ''[[Wyverntongue Chalice]]'' and ''[[Flying Blade]]''.{{cite book/Elminster Must Die/MMP|245-246|23}} 

Unknwon to anyone, the evil archmage [[Manshoon]] had resolved to slay Gaskur for one of his intrigues: he was going to send [[Talane]] to murder him.{{cite book/Elminster Must Die/MMP|272|26}} Gaskur's body was brought to Marlin afterwards; according to the watch, he was murdered on a roof, and the word "[[talane]]" scrawled on that same roof with his blood before he was kicked onto the floor.{{cite book/Elminster Must Die/MMP|303-306|29}}
